## Purpose within BIAV

Graphify fills the "黑池索引" (Black Pool Index) pillar of BIAV's
Black Pool system — the AI-readable index layer that produces a
queryable knowledge graph from code, docs, papers, and multimodal
corpora. See `memory/blackpool-architecture.md` requirement #3.

## Relationship to Silver Core knowledge_graph.py

The two systems are complementary, not replacements:

- Silver Core's `scripts/knowledge_graph.py` owns
  curated game lore, decisions history, and human-maintained graphs.
- graphify-ext owns
  automated extraction from code and documentation with Tree-sitter AST
  (23 languages including Lua, relevant for Morimens game scripts) and
  Leiden community detection (no embeddings required).

Both will expose tools via the Silver Core MCP server
(`scripts/mcp_server.py`); consumers need not distinguish sources.

